<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Gasanov Visits Germany </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702195294 Baku Radio Baku Network in Azeri 1700 GMT 27 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Azerbaijan Ministry of Foreign Affairs Press 
Service has announced that Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov has 
arrived in Germany on an official visit. Gasanov was invited to 
visit that country by Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel. 
  In a statement to Radio Liberty, the German ambassador 
extraordinary and plenipotentiary in Azerbaijan said that 
Gasanov and Kinkel will hold talks on the mutual cooperation 
between Germany and Azerbaijan in various fields. They will 
also discuss the situation in the region, how to end the dispute 
between Azerbaijan and Armenia, and [words indistinct]. The 
ambassador said that during their talks with Gasanov, the German 
officials will maintain the view that the dispute between 
Azerbaijan and Armenia should be resolved within the CSCE 
framework. He also stressed that the two foreign ministers are 
expected to sign an agreement on the safeguarding of Germany's 
interests in Azerbaijan and Azerbaijan's interests in Germany. 
In general, the prospects of mutual cooperation between Germany 
and Azerbaijan in various fields have inspired hope for the 
future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

