<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Begins Aid for Dismantling Nuclear Weapons </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502155894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1517 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev February 25 UKRINFORM-TASS -- The United States 
has begun implementing its aid programme to Ukraine within the 
frame of the agreement on Safety and Security in Dismantling 
Nuclear Weapons in Ukraine (SSD). This agreement was signed by 
the U.S. and Ukraine in October of last year. The American aid 
has arrived in the form of fuel for transportation and for the 
operation of equipment to be used in the dismantling of 
Ukraine's nuclear weapons. 

</TEXT>

