<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Condemns Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602154894 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1300 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday, Ukraine's Foreign Affairs Ministry 
disseminated a statement resolutely condemning the bloody event, 
which took place in the town of Hebron when Palestinians were at 
prayer. The statement by Ukraine's foreign policy department 
expresses deep sympathy to the families of those who died and 
the hope that the injured will recover. It emphasizes that any 
terrorist actions, whatever their aim might be, and whoever they 
are carried out by, are not justified. 
  Ukraine's Foreign Affairs Ministry has appealed to the 
Palestinian and Israeli sides with a call not to resort to 
self-seeking emotions, and expressed the hope for a continuation 
of the Arab-Israeli dialogue with the aim of achieving a 
peaceful settlement in the Near East. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

