<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ukraine, China Sign Economic Cooperation Protocol </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602121794 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1900 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Affairs Ministry Press Center has 
reported that at the invitation of China's Internal Trade 
Ministry, a delegation from Ukraine's Agriculture and Food 
Ministry is over there. Employees from this department are in 
the delegation, and so are representatives from our state's 
business circles. The delegation has already held a number of 
meetings at the Ministries of Internal Trade and Agriculture of 
the People's Republic of China. The sides determined specific 
directions of joint work in the sphere of production and 
scientific-technical cooperation -- setting up joint 
enterprises, introducing new agrarian technologies, and the 
exchange of information. 
  During the course of talks a protocol was signed on 
economic, 
scientific-technical, and production cooperation. 

</TEXT>

