<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zlenko Postpones Polish Visit Due to Lysenko Trial </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502222894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1909 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502222894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian and Polish foreign ministers had a 
telephone conversation on Friday during which it was decided to 
postpone the visit of Ukrainian Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko 
to Warsaw from February 28 to late March. 
  According to sources close to the Ukrainian Foreign 
Ministry, 
the visit was put off due to the legal proceedings against an 
officer of the Ukrainian Security Service (the so-called case of 
Lysenko) continuing in Warsaw from January 19. 
  Anatoliy Lysenko and his family left for Poland in August, 
1993, on a private invitation and was arrested immediately after 
he crossed the border. 
  Lysenko has been accused of spying for Ukraine. The 
Ukrainian Security Service refutes the accusations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

