<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Conditions Participation in Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502154294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1450 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM correspondent Viktor Demidenko for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev February 25 TASS -- Ukrainian President Leonid 
Kravchuk conditioned his participation in presidential elections 
and said it is first necessary to elect a new parliament and 
determine the powers of the future president. 
  "My decision on participation in early presidential 
elections 
depends on many factors", he told reporters on Friday. 
  "First and foremost we have to elect a new parliament and 
appoint a new Cabinet of Ministers", he stressed and added that 
any candidate for the presidency "should know his future powers" 
before joining the election campaign. 
  "At present they (the powers) have not been determined. If 
the new president is elected according to the acting 
constitution, the new parliament is sure to raise the question 
about the powers of the president, the Supreme Soviet and the 
government. The powers of local heads of administrations have 
not been determined either", he said. 

</TEXT>

