1200 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2702152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian ambassador to Russia, Volodymyr 
Kryzhanovshyy, refuted a report that Leonid Kravchuk has refused 
to take part in the upcoming presidential elections of the 
republic. 
  In his words, Ukrainian president came out in favor of 
postponing the election of the head of state. If his opinion is 
disregarded, he may refuse to run for presidency, said 
Kryzhanovshyy. 

