<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Holds Meeting With Crimean Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2402124994 Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA in Ukrainian 22 Feb 
94 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> AU2402124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev DEMOKRATYCHNA UKRAYINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [UKRINFORM report: "A Meeting Between Members of the </F>
Ukrainian and Crimean Governments"] 
  [Text] Under the chairmanship of Ukraine's acting prime 
minister, Yukhym Zvyahilskyy, Ukraine's Cabinet of Ministers 
held a meeting to discuss the fulfillment of the Ukrainian 
president's commissions on the results of his talks with the 
president of the Crimean Republic. Those present included 
Ukraine's vice premiers Vasyl Yevtukhov, Valentyn Landyk, 
secretary of the Ukrainian presidential administration Mykola 
Khomenko, and other members of the government. The working 
group of the Crimean government was headed at the meeting by 
acting chairman of the Crimean Republic's Council of Ministers 
Anatoliy Franchuk. The participants in the conference 
considered and discussed a whole series of questions, including 
problems associated with the implementation of the agreement on 
budget relationships between the government of Ukraine and the 
government of the Crimean Republic; on the allocation of 110 
billion karbovantsi to clear the debt in financing the program 
for stabilizing the Crimean economy and in financing measures 
associated with the return of Crimean Tatars, Germans, and other 
deported peoples; on the division of state property among 
Ukraine and the Crimean Republic; on the determination of 
sources for covering the expenditure in hard currency of 
enterprises situated on the territory of the Crimean Republic; 
on questions of canceling restrictions for Ukrainian citizens' 
entering the city of Sevastopol; and on measures for stabilizing 
the functioning of a number of branches of the Crimean 
Republic's economic complex. 

</TEXT>

