<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Adopts Resolution on 1994 Social, Economic Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602121694 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in English 
2200 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Cabinet of Ministers adopted a resolution on the 
1994 plan of Ukraine's social and economic development, the 
presidential cabinet press service reported. The plan 
specifies, in particular, the state contracts and orders 
amounts, including those of basic agricultural products and 
foods. It also specifies the amounts of centralized capital 
investments and new production facilities to be commissioned. 
  The plans reportedly contains provisions for enhancing state 
discipline by subjects of economic activities involving, in 
particular, pricing discipline in fuel supplies to Ukraine under 
intergovernmental agreements with exporter nations. 
  As the presidential cabinet press service disclosed, 
President Kravchuk provided a formal additional submission to 
the parliament of Ukraine's accedence to the Nuclear 
Nonproliferation Treaty. 

</TEXT>

