<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Approves Nikitov as Administration Head </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602162294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1109 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 26 Feb -- Federation Council deputies today 
approved Vladimir Nikitov as head of the chamber's 
administration. The 43-year-old candidate of technical sciences 
was adviser to Vladimir Shumeyko when he was first deputy 
chairman of the government. He has also had considerable 
experience of working in the Supreme Soviet. 
  In reply to deputies' questions about guaranteeing their 
parliamentary activity, Vladimir Nikitov said, in particular, 
that the question of deputies' badges had not yet been decided. 
The matter is being held up because of their cost: The proposed 
draft badge containing precious metals will cost half a million 
[currency not specified]. 

</TEXT>

