<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Commission on Ossetian Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502215994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1840 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 25 TASS -- A report of the 
Federation Council's Commission for Studies of the situation in 
Northern ossetia and Ingushetia was presented today to the Upper 
Chamber of the Russian Parliament by Commission head Valeriy 
Fateyev. 
  In his opinion, the main regional problem is refugees. 
Fateyev stressed the Ingush and North ossetian presidents can 
agree between themselves on the return of refugees to places of 
their permanent residence. 
  North Ossetian president Akhsarbek galazov supported the 
pronouncement and said "the interested sides should have a 
chance to agree between themselves and the federal bodies should 
listen to the opinion of regional representatives". He added 
they have agreed with Ingush leader Ruslan Aushev on further 
negotiations. 
  Aushev agreed with Galazov, but said "they should remember 
about refugees". In his words, the participation in the 
conciliatory commission has brought no results and the North 
Ossetian president should name the exact date of his solution of 
the Ingush refugee problem. 
  The Russian Parliament deputies decided to continue the 
problem analysis in committees and discuss their proposals at 
the chamber meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

