<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko Comments on Federation Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602172094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1628 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 26 TASS -- The third meeting of the 
Russian Federation Council, which lasted for only three days, 
has shown "the chamber proceeds from the urgent needs and its 
ability to help the reforms with laws," Council Speaker Vladimir 
Shumeyko told an exclusive ITAR-TASS interview. 
  A reason for active work of the chamber is the "absence of 
factionalism and division on party principle. It is not 
important for us who suggests a proposal if the latter is good," 
he said. 
  In the words of Shumeyko, the presidential message to the 
Federal Assembly will be discussed at a council plenary 
scheduled for March 15. The deputies have discussed some 
problems related to the message, including a resolution on 
measures against crime in the Russian Federation. 
  The deputies believe that order is even more important than 
the economic reform. In their opinion, it is a "comprehensive 
problem that starts from the question of power". They favor the 
creation of a solid system of vertical power in order to control 
implementation of resolutions. 
  Shumeyko thinks that anti-crime measures include aspects of 
the economic reform. While the old system has been ruined and a 
new one has not been formed, the use of laws to expand criminal 
activities should be prevented. 
  These also include the border issue which is to be settled 
by 
the Federation Council. Unestablished borders enable any person 
to penetrate into the Russian Federation and carry arms or drugs. 
  The introduction of a state of emergency is another 
prerogative of the upper parliament chamber. A lot of arms have 
been accumulated in the state of emergency zones, which also 
results in the increased crime rate. Shumeyko does not exclude 
parliamentary hearings on enhanced measures against crime may 
result in the parliament's proposal to the president to 
introduce the state of emergency in some Russian areas in order 
to remove arms from the residents. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-14771 </DOCNO>
