<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nuclear Agency Head: No Need To Stop Ignalina Reactor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2502210794 Vilnius ELTA in English 1920 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2502210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News Bulletin" No. 445] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius, Feb 25, ELTA -- "There is no necessity to 
stop the second reactor of Ignalina nuclear plant", Povilas 
Vaisnys, head of Lithuania's State Nuclear Agency Inspectorate 
VATESI, told ELTA. 
  "If Lithuania had troubles to get electricity from other 
sources, the reactor would not be stopped", he said. 
  A little amount of steam can leak because of bad sealed 
measurers of flow in the technological channel. It does not 
hinder safe exploitation of the reactor at all, Vaisnys said. 
  Anyway, the reactor is to be stopped on Friday, 9.00 p.m. 
Vaisnys said there was a need to know the reasons even of such a 
little radioactive leak. 
  He mentioned one more reason of the stoppage - the first 
reactor is due to be stopped next month for routine repairs and 
"we need to be sure the second reactor operates without 
problems". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-14774 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov039_h_94001" </HT>


