<H3> <TI>   `High Turnout' Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2702204994 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1850 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2702204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Comrat, BASAPRESS 27/2/1994 -- Some 50 percent of 
40,000 eligible voters in Comrat came to vote this morning at 
the 33 polling centres in this town. Piotr Ivanov, acting 
secretary of the district Executive committee, told BASAPRESS. 
Despite forecasts, there was a high turn-out at all polling 
stations. Ivanov pointed out that the voters did not follow the 
political games of certain local leaders who called on people 
not to participate in the elections. Ender Arat, general consul 
of Turkey in Moldova, arrived in Comrat a day before election 
day. He called on all political forces and movements during a 
meeting with local leaders to be reasonable. Also, Arat 
emphasized the importance of Gagauzians in creating the new 
Moldovan Parliament. 

</TEXT>

