<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chelyabinsk Prosecutor Resigns Over Amnesty Ruling </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802095894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0932 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yevgeniy Tkachenko] </F>
  [Text] Chelyabinsk, 28 Feb -- Chelyabinsk Oblast Prosecutor 
Gennadiy Likhachev has submitted his resignation. Speaking on 
local radio today, he stressed that this step was brought about 
by the fact that he did not agree with the political amnesty 
declared by the State Duma. In his view, "the procuracy has 
once again been made hostage to political intrigues." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-14787 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov039_d_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-039 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  28 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

