<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Caucasus Spokesman on Amnesty Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2702193894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1753 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2702193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The General Secretary of the Assembly of Democratic 
Forces of the North Caucasus, Shmidt Dzoblayev, has said that 
the "economic and political situation compels the Russian 
president to impose a state of emergency and save the country 
from fresh political upheavals." 
  In a statement published on Sunday Dzoblayev said that the 
State Duma's resolution on granting amnesty to participants in 
last October's riots poses "an act of absolute disrespect for 
the law, unprecedented in political practice." 
  According to him, as a result of it "the confrontation 
between the various political forces and branches of power will 
inevitably grow, and the consolidation of power institutions 
which began to take shape when the new Constitution was adopted 
will collapse". 
  As Dzoblayev said, Sergey Shakhray must share the 
responsibility for this with the "communist obscurantists". "His 
further being in charge of the ethnic policy department is 
absurd," the statement says. 

</TEXT>

