<F P=102>  LD2702212194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2111 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2702212194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Yarushin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 28 TASS -- Ruslan Aushev has been 
re-elected to the post of Ingush president, ITAR-TASS learned 
from well-informed sources in the Ingush capital of Nazran. 
Vice-President Boris Agapov also managed to retain his post. 
  According to preliminary election results as of 10:00 p.m., 
the turnout made up over 70 percent. 
  The final results of the presidential and vice-presidential 
elections, as well as of the consitutional referendum are not to 
be available until Tuesday, March 1. Results of parliamentary 
elections will be published in about a week and a half. 

