<H3> <TI>   North Ossetian President Praises Yeltsin Reform Note </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2702204394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1948 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2702204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS Correspondent Valery Shanyev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz February 27 TASS -- "The implementation 
of the message by Russian President Boris Yeltsin aiming to 
strengthen power at all levels is designed to speed up economic 
reforms in Russia," North Ossetian President Askharbek Galazov 
told ITAR-TASS upon returning from Moscow. 
  "The most important thing now is to develop a mechanism for 
implementing this message," Galazov stressed. "The president 
counts on the Russian Constitution. Boris Yeltsin has confirmed 
that the state's unity and integrity can be preserved on the 
basis of Russia's federated arrangement," he said. 
  The president shared gave his assessment to the activities 
of 
the parliamentary commission in the state of emergency zone in 
North Ossetia and Ingushetia. The North Ossetian and Ingush 
presidents are capable of settling their differences without any 
mediation, he emphasised. They can solve all complicated issues 
by themselves. "A negotiating process between the two republics 
has got underway, it should be continued," Galazov said. 
  Commenting on the results of the Zheleznovodsk meeting of 
North Caucasian leader with the participation of the chief of 
the Russian president's staff, Galazov described it as "another 
attempt to settle relations between North Ossetia and Ingushetia 
by peaceful means." According to him, "North Ossetia is ready 
to work consistently for establishing normal relations with all 
its neighbours. I insist that the problem of refugees cannot be 
solved by use of force. The final word is to be said by 
reconciliation commissions," he emphasised. 

</TEXT>

