<H3> <TI>   To Meet Ingush Counterpart </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802171794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1356 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz February 28 TASS -- President Akhsarbek 
Galazov of North Ossetia has reiterated his decision to meet 
Ingush President Ruslan Aushev for discussing problems dealing 
with the settlement of relations between the two republics. 
Speaking today at a meeting with members of the government, the 
presidium of the republican Supreme soviet (parliament) and 
heads of local government bodies, he stressed, however, that the 
meeting should be carefully prepared, and questions to be 
discussed by the two sides should be thoroughly analysed. In 
his opinion, the return of refugees to the populated localities 
of the Prigorodnyy district is the most complicated of them. It 
should be tackled in a comprehensive way on the basis of 
Kislovodsk accords. 
  "The presidents of North Ossetia and Ingushetia will be able 
to tackle their problems by themselves, without intermediaries, 
to decide matters dealing with the settlement of relations 
between the two nations and to make all the problems clear. The 
negotiating process between the republics has been started, and 
it should be continued," Galazov said. 
  Speaking about the current situation in the part of North 
Ossetia, where a state of emergency will be in effect until 
March 31, Galazov pointed out that it continued to be 
comparatively stable. Russia's peace-making forces in 
cooperation with local law-enforcement agencies are keeping the 
situation under control. 

</TEXT>

