<H3> <TI>   Planned Terrorist Attack on Sobchak Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602190994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1759 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By unidentified ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg February 26 TASS -- St. Petersburg 
newspapers reported today at a Friday [25 February] briefing at 
the Federal Counter-intelligence Service's department despite 
all the refutations. The briefing told correspondents about 
details of the detention of five terrorists on the eve of 2 
February near the Kazan cathedral. 
  In the words of head of the service department's division 
against terrorism Aleksandr Kuznetsov, the detained, some of 
whom participated in the October 1993 events in Moscow, prepared 
an armed attack at a Petersburg police station. The attack was 
expected to seize arms to be later used in an attempt upon the 
life of Petersburg Mayor Anatoliy Sobchak and an attack at the 
Moscow government house. The information is taken from 
materials of the Petersburg counter-intelligence service. 
  According to mass media reports, the individuals were 
detained right after their attack at the sentry-box of the Zarya 
scientific-production amalgamation, where they seized five 
revolvers and 2,000 cartridges. 
  Kuznetsov did not comment on political hidden motives of the 
terrorists' actions in the interests of the investigation. 
However, he said intentions of the group, whose youngest member 
is 39 years old and the oldest is 47, were serious. 

</TEXT>

