<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reaction to Duma Amesty Decision Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Poltoranin Terms Decision `Thoughtless' </H4>
<F P=102> LD2502165694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1609 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 25 TASS -- "The thoughtless and 
impulsive decision of the State Duma on amnesty may entail the 
most grave consequences for Russia," chairman of the Duma 
Committee on Information Policy and Communications Mikhail 
Poltoranin told an exclusive ITAR-TASS interview here today. 
  The initiators of "political amnesty made a fool" not only 
of 
themselves but also of those they supported; "Both the August 
1991 putsch plotters and participants in the bloody October 
developments should plead guilty in order to become free," said 
Poltoranin. 
  In the opinion of Poltoranin, the opposition worked most for 
the liberation of Aleksandr Rutskoy as a "national leader". But 
the situation will also be used by people who fired at unarmed 
people. 
  The amnesty resolution is an act of humiliation and 
discrediting of the authorities, not only those executive, said 
Poltoranin. "It is a blow on the law-enforcement bodies and the 
legal system of the state," he noted. 
  Intruding into competence of the court bodies, the State 
Duma 
did not think about consequences. The latter may not only occur 
in political life but also affect the interior bodies, which 
fight against crime risking the lives of their staffers. 
  Poltoranin said he is against "global amnesties". In his 
opinion, some 20,000 people will be freed from prisons and 
penitentiaries to make the life of law-abiding citizens even 
more dangerous. 

</TEXT>

