<H3> <TI>   Khasbulatov, Rutskoy, Other Prisoners Released </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602151394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1456 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Anna Melnikova and Aleksandr </F>
Kharchenko] 
  [Text] Moscow February 26 TASS -- Ruslan Khasbulatov, 
Aleksandr Rutskoy, Albert Makashev, Andrey Dunayev, Viktor 
Anpilov and Vladislav Achalov were freed from the Lefortovo 
investigation ward today in accordance with a State Duma 
resolution on amnesty. 
  All the accused who agree with the State Duma resolution 
will 
be freed from Lefortovo today, Deputy Russian Procurator General 
Vladimir Kravtsev told ITAR-TASS. 
  It is Kravtsev who sets free persons arrested after the 
October 1993 revolt, as Russian Procurator General Aleksey 
Kazannik sent in his resignation earlier today. Kravtsev has 
told a news conference today the four deputies of the Russian 
procurator general are at one with Kazannik and are ready to 
resign as well. 

</TEXT>

