<H3> <TI>   Comment Upon Release </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602193294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1800 GMT 
26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today Ruslan Khasbulatov, Aleksandr Rutskoy, Albert 
Makashov, Andrey Dunayev, Viktor Anpilov, Vladislav Achalov, and 
Ilya Konstantinov left the investigation ward of the Lefortovo 
prison. Aleksandr Barkashov was released today from the 
Matrosskaya Tishina prison. They have been released in 
accordance with the State Duma's anmesty resolution. 
  What is the mood of the former prisoners who came back to 
freedom today? Here are some statements of those released: 
  Anpilov said that if the prices during his imprisonment have 
gone up, he will struggle on to the victorious end. He sees his 
task in summoning the working collectives to fight against the 
regime. 
  Replying to the question on what he intends to do in the 
near 
future, Aleksandr Barkashov said he would do the same as before. 
  Rutskoy described his release from prison as a return to the 
people. 
  Khasbulatov told journalists that he did not think he was to 
blame. 
  Makashov said that he intends to go home to Samara for a 
rest. 

</TEXT>

