<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anpilov Comments on Release </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602202994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1823 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At 17:15 Ilya Konstantinov, leader of National 
Salvation Front, left the investigation prison Lefortovo. A 
crowd which has gathered at the prison's gates actually embraced 
him. Saying "Thank you, thank you," Konstantinov came up to 
his car with great difficulties and moved away. 
  When asked by journalists who will become Russia's next 
president, leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy who was staying near Lefortovo answered 
that the people would make their choice. In Zhirinovskiy's 
words, the people will have to choose either him or Rutskoy. 
  Leader of the Labor Russia and Russian Communist Labor Party 
Viktor Anpilov left Lefortovo at 17:25, just after Konstantinov. 
Hundreds of his supporters welcomed Anpilov. 
  At an improvised meeting Anpilov declared: "The will of the 
single Soviet people has torn us from the torture-chambers. We 
have not recognized our guilt and do not recognize it. There is 
no guilt. We have chosen amnesty for the sake of accord and 
reconciliation in the society." 
  "If I leave the prison and see that prices have dropped and 
people live better then Yeltsin was right. If prices raised and 
people live worse then I shall continue my struggle till the 
victory," declared Anpilov. 
  Accompanied by a 400-strong crowd of his supporters Anpilov 
left the square before the investigation prison on foot. 
  In his interview with Interfax Anpilov said that now his 
nearest task is "to organize working staffs for struggle with 
the regime." He intends "to travel throughout the country and to 
meet with working people." 
  Anpilov believes that now Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin has 
occupied that place on the political arena which earlier was 
occupied by Ruslan Khasbulatov. 
  According to Anpilov, it is necessary to hold early 
presidential elections because there is a new Constitution and a 
new president should swear on the new Constitution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

