<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kostikov Says Release `Blasphemous' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602195094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1851 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 26 Feb (ITAR-TASS) -- Vyacheslav Kostikov, 
the press secretary of the Russian president described the 
release of organizers and participants of the events in October 
1993 from Lefortovo as a blasphemous action. He said today that 
people whose hands and conscience have been party to bloodshed, 
people who were ready to push Russia into the bloody maelstrom 
of the civil war have been released without trial. 
  The press secretary of the Russian president believes that 
the State Duma and in the first place those parties who 
initiated and supported this blasphemous action are wholly 
responsible for this act of moral violence. This is the first 
time in the history of world parliamentarism. He believes that 
the State Duma is becoming the coparticipant of unlawfulness. 
  Having abused the people's trust, the deputies have for the 
the first time in history -- the statement he has issued says -- 
taken the side of evil-doers against the state. The State Duma, 
which was called upon to be the guardian of law, the initiator 
of civil accord, and a participant in building a rule-of-law 
state, has by its own will removed from the framework of justice 
persons accused of the gravest of state crimes, preferring hasty 
political demarches to a just court. 
  The document points out that an outrage has been committed 
against justice, public opinion has been rejected, and the 
opinion of a president elected by popular vote has been 
challenged. The haste and urgency with which the State Duma 
strove to achieve the immediate implementation of its 
resolution, and in essence the covering up of the evil done to 
Russia, is evidence not of the Duma's desire to achieve civil 
peace and accord, but of its effective incitement to political 
extremism. 
  In the unlawful situation that has come about, the president 
of Russia reserves the right to act in accordance with the 
powers granted to him by the Constitution, Kostikov declared. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

