<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Preparing `Certain Actions' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802115194 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Russian president's press service will start 
holding regular briefings from today. Boris Yeltsin's press 
secretary Vyacheslav Kostikov and presidential aide Georgiy 
Satarov discussed a very topical and timely subject with 
journalists today -- the defense of democracy and human rights. 
  As ITAR-TASS has just reported, Georgiy Satarov, the head of 
state's aide, told the briefing that Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin has prepared certain actions aimed at defending the 
democratic state and society. He refused to specify the form in 
which these measures would be carried out. However, Yuriy 
Baturin, the president's assistant for national security, added 
that these steps might even be taken today. He described press 
speculation that this would include a TV address as being close 
to the truth. 

</TEXT>

