<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Accepts Resignation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602192094 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1800 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] I have just received an INTERFAX report in the 
studio. It says that Boris Yeltsin has accepted the resignation 
of Procurator General Aleksey Kazannikov. 
  This is followed by a report from the presidential press 
service which says that the edict also decrees that Aleksey 
Nikolayevich Ilyushenko be presented to the Federation Council 
as a candidate for nomination to the post of procurator general 
of the Russian Federation. 
  Until the procurator general is appointed, Ilyushenko is 
entrusted with carrying out his duties. 
  Under another edict, Ilyushenko is released from the post of 
head of the control directorate of the president's 
administration. 

</TEXT>

