<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kazannik Explains Resignation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802132094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1244 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yuriy Scherban] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, February 28 (TASS) -- "I have acted in full 
compliance with law and my conscience is clear. Let those who 
do not rely on law blush for their conduct," said Alexey 
Kazannik, former Russian prosecutor general, as he parted with 
his colleagues on Monday. Kazannik's resignation was accepted 
by Russian president on February 26. 
  Addressing his colleagues, Kazannik explained his 
resignation, saying that he had been put under pressure from 
high-ranking officials from the president's administration who 
demanded that the resolution on amnesty adopted by the State 
Duma be suspended. "As a supporter and authorised official of 
President Yeltsin, I had to carry out any presidential orders, 
even of they were illegal," Kazannik said. 
  On the other hand, Kazannik referred to officials of the 
prosecutor's office who believe that "there are no legal grounds 
to do anything against this amnesty." Facing a complex dilemma, 
Kazannik tried to "personally get in touch with the Russian 
president and explain the situation to him." However, he failed 
to do this and decided to resign from his post. 
  Kazannik declared that Aleksey Ilushenko, temporarily 
appointed to the post of the prosecutor general by the Russian 
president, as a chairman of the control department of the 
president's administration, had called on him to prevent putting 
the resolution an amnesty into effect. This "illegal" demand, 
as Kazannik put it, was made by participants in an emergency 
meeting held to discuss the only one problem -- how to prevent 
the amnesty and who adopted a decision not to let prisoners out 
of Lefortovo whatever the cost might be. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

