<H3> <TI>   Acting Prosecutor General Appointed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2702061994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0549 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2702061994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 27 TASS -- Vladimir Shumeyko, 
chairman of the Federation Council, has consented to the 
president's proposal to appoint Aleksey Ilyushenko as acting 
prosecutor-general of the Russian Federation. 
  It has become known from reliable sources that the decision 
was taken "on the basis of the president's recommendation 
pending the consideration of an item to this effect at a 
Federation Council meeting in accordance with Article 102 of the 
Russian Constitution". 
  The need to appoint an acting prosecutor-general arose in 
view of the resignation of Aleksey Kazannik from the post on 
Saturday. 
  Kazannik disagrees with the release, by a State Duma 
decision, of those guilty of the October 3-4, 1993, bloodshed in 
Moscow, and regards it as unlawful and uncoordinated with law 
enforcement agencies. 

</TEXT>

