<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shakhray Gives Party Program at PRES Congress </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602211294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1818 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The First Congress of Russia's Unity and Concord 
Party [PRES] opened in Moscow on Saturday. Taking part are 220 
delegates from 66 regions of Russia. 
  They intend to discuss the draft of a party program and the 
results of the elections to the Federal Assembly, amend the 
rules and elect the steering bodies, and work out the party's 
strategy and tactics for local elections. 
  In his speech on the party program, its leader Sergey 
Shakhray declared that his party is "a national conservative 
organization, respecting such traditional values as state, 
family, property, and morality." In his words, the party aims 
at keeping Russia as a state by recognizing the economic, 
political, and cultural diversity of its regions. 
  Shakhray proposed endorsing only "the framework of the 
program" at this stage and to finalize it at the 2d Congress, 
planned for the spring this year. Before that the program could 
be explained in the party's regional branches. 
  As a delegate has revealed to Interfax, the money for the 
forum have come "from the party fund and from the commercial 
structures, sharing the party's goals and tasks." 

</TEXT>

