<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputies Discuss Constitution, Electoral Law, Trade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2502154894 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1300 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2502154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mikhail Rutkowski] </F>
  [Excerpts] At the beginning of today's debate, the floor 
was taken by Supreme Soviet Chairman Mechyslaw Ivanovich Hryb. 
He appealed to people's deputies and journalists not to support 
abortion, while voting on the draft constitution that is to be 
adopted by our parliament. I will recall that in their ballots, 
deputies are being asked to define their position on the 
legislative, executive, and juridical authorities of the 
Republic of Belarus, and respond to whether our state should 
become a presidential republic. The results of the voting will 
be announced next week. 
  Having heard the speeches delivered in the miscellaneous 
section, deputies continued the debate on amendments to the 
electoral law. After that, they began to discuss the Supreme 
Soviet draft resolution on the volume of foreign debt and trends 
in the use and repayments of foreign credits. The draft 
resolution specifies that the volume of foreign debt of the 
Republic of Belarus will amount to $2 billion until the end of 
1994. [passage omitted] 
  Because today is Friday, deputies voted to shorten the 
working day. The session concluded at 1700 [1200 GMT]. 
Deputies will reconvene at the Oval Hall of the House of 
Government next Tuesday. 

</TEXT>

