<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rakhmanov, CSCE Secretary General Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502115994 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 0500 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tajik </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday, Imamali Rakhmanov, the head of state and 
Supreme Council chairman of the Republic of Tajikistan received 
CSCE Secretary General Wilhelm Hoeynck who is on a visit to our 
republic. The latter is on a visit to some Central Asian states. 
  Imamali Rakhmanov highly appraised the assistance of the 
CSCE 
to Tajikistan in the course of the meeting that was held in an 
atmosphere of mutual understanding. Imamali Rakhmanov said that 
the republic is ready to use the assistance of this 
authoritative international organization to organize democratic 
structures and develop market economy relations. 
  Both sides unanimously expressed that cooperation between 
the 
CSCE and Tajikistan should be further developed. 
  Rashid Olimov, the foreign affairs minister of the republic 
and Karimjon Yuldoshev, the state adviser to the head of state 
on political and international issues were present at the 
meeting. 
  Abdulmadjid Samadov, the chairman of the Council of 
Ministers 
of the republic received CSCE Secretary General Wilhelm Hoeynck 
on the same day. Abdulmadjid Samadov familiarized Wilhelm 
Hoeynck with the present economic situation in the republic, and 
pointed out the adherence of the republic to strengthening 
market economy relations. 
  CSCE Secretary General William Hoeynck met Foreign Affairs 
Minister Rashid Olimov on the same day. 
  Wilhelm Hoeynck gave a news conference for local and foreign 
journalists after the end of his working visit. 

</TEXT>

