<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses Events With Warren Christopher </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103124694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1106 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0103124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As Russia's Foreign Ministry reported to Interfax, 
on the initiative of the American side, Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev and U.S. State Secretary Warren Christopher had a 
telephone talk on Monday [28 February] evening. 
  The parties discussed the Bosnian settlement and the 
situation in the Middle East. In particular, they stressed the 
need to strictly for strict fulfillment of the UN Security 
Council resolutions by all Bosnian parties. Moscow and 
Washington intend to encourage striving for compromise solutions 
in the spirit of goodwill. 
  Given the latest events in the Middle East, the importance 
was recognized of preserving the negotiating process and 
strengthening security guarantees for the population in the Gaza 
Strip and Jericho with an appropriate international presence. 

</TEXT>

