<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   `No Real Evidence' Ames Spied for Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103132794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1231 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0103132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow March 1 TASS -- Experts from Russia's Foreign 
Intelligence Service regard the publication of information about 
Aldrich Ames' alleged involvement in the transfer of technology 
to Russia for the development of a supersecret weapon as a drive 
launched by U.S. secret services with a view to attracting the 
public attention to the "Ames case". 
  The reason for this and other actions, the Russian experts 
believe, is the more understandable as, according to data 
available with them, U.S. secret services so far have no real 
evidence of Mr. Ames' involvement in spying for Russia. 

</TEXT>

