<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Adviser Says Government Regrets Incident in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2802130394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0915 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2802130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 28 Feb (EFE) -- Anatoliy Krasikov, chief of 
the Russian Presidency's information service, says that Russia 
"regrets" the incident which took place today in northwestern 
Bosnia where four Serbian airplanes were downed by two U.S. 
F-16's. 
  "We regret the incident because Russia is working toward a 
peaceful solution of the conflict in former Yugoslavia," the 
ranking official said. 
  Krasikov added that the Russian Government, through either 
the Foreign Ministry or Defense Ministry, will issue an official 
statement on the incident. 

</TEXT>

