<H3> <TI>   Latest Developments Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802133794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1313 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents] </F>
  [Text] Paris/Rome/Jakarta February 28 TASS -- Bosnian 
Serbs, backed by helicopters and armoured personnel carriers, 
launched an attack Monday morning against the Bosnian Muslim 
town of Maglaj. 
  The town besieged by Serbian and Croatian units is under 
heavy gun fire, the FRANCE-PRESSE news agency reported today. 
  The American aircraft carrier "Saratoga" with 70 war planes 
aboard has cut short her visit to Trieste in Italy and is 
heading towards the cost of former Yugoslavia, the Italian news 
agency AGI reported from Rome today. 
  The agency said it was connected with the morning shooting 
down of four Bosnian Serbs' aircraft by NATO. 
  Indonesia, currently chairing the Non-Alignment Movement, 
demanded an urgent session of the UN Security Council to lift 
the embargo on weapons deliveries to Bosnian Muslims, TASS 
reported from Jakarta today. 

</TEXT>

