<H3> <TI>   Foreign Affairs Ministry Statement on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802163294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1545 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 28 Feb (ITAR-TASS) -- A statement by 
Russia's Foreign Affairs Ministry was circulated here today 
which said: 
  "According to the information we have so far, aircraft 
guarding the no-fly zone in Bosnia-Herzegovina air space this 
moring shot down four planes that had violated the zone and 
bombed the area at the town of Travnik, that is, in the zone of 
armed clashes between Muslims and Croats. 
  Furthermore, it is alleged that these planes could belong to 
Bosnian Serbs, though the latter's military command denies this. 
The circumstances surrounding the incident are now being 
clarified. 
  Whichever side carried out the military sortie over Bosnia- 
Herzegovina, violating the resolutions of the UN Security 
Council relating to the no-fly zone, it carries all the 
responsiblity for what has happened. 

</TEXT>

