<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Statement on Situation in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802184094 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1800 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802184094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] [Unidentified correspondent] How does Russian 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev assess the situation in Bosnia 
now? 
  [Begin Kozyrev recording] We are against the use of 
aircraft, 
and we have a proposal that the use of aircraft should be 
forbidden in the strictest terms in all conflict areas. In 
particular, we were among the initiators of the adoption of the 
resolution on a flight-free zone, i.e. on the nonuse of aircraft 
in Bosnia. Hence, whichever side used these aircraft, it has to 
proceed from the assumption that full responsibility lies with 
the violator of, in this case, the Security Council resolution. 
Certainly this episode is yet more evidence that the road in 
Bosnia should lie not in the escalation of violence, in the use 
of aviation etc., but only in looking for a political 
settlement. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

