<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Ossetia Ready for Talks With Ingushetia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802153594 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1200 GMT 
28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a meeting of members of the Cabinet of Ministers, 
North Ossetian President Akhsarbek Galazov said he was ready for 
dialogue with Ingushetia President Ruslan Aushev. He said: We 
need to implement the presidential decree and the decision by 
the Russian Government on returning refugees to their places of 
abode on the territory of North Ossetia and Ingushetia. Galazov 
categorically ruled out the possibility of granting additional 
powers to the interim administration on the territory of North 
Ossetia and Ingushetia and, for the first time, called for the 
lifting of the state of emergency regime on part of the 
territory of North Ossetia. 

</TEXT>

