  [Text] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of the Liberal 
Democratic Party, told Interfax that he had appealed Monday [28 
February] against the ruling of the Shchyolkovo District Court, 
Moscow Region. 
  The court canceled the election result in the electoral 
district where Zhirinovskiy won the December 12 elections. The 
reason for the ruling is that a Yabloko bloc candidate resigned 
from the election race in favor of the Russia's Choice candidate 
but his name remained in the electoral bulletin. 

