<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Purpose of Kravchuk U.S. Visit Explained </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802152694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1428 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 28 February, Anton Buteyko, adviser to the 
Ukrainian president on international affairs, commented on 
Leonid Kravchuk's visit to the United States to a UNIAN 
correspondent. In particular, Anton Buteyko said: "There is a 
change for the better in the attitude to Ukraine on the part of 
United States and other Western states. Previously they were 
interested only in the situation concerning nuclear weapons, 
whereas now they are interested in full-scale economic 
cooperation and assistance for Ukraine in connection with the 
economic crisis. The main aim of the visit is to raise both 
countries' economic relations to a new level. It is expected 
that a number of agreements will be signed: on the legal basis 
of Western investments, avoiding double taxation, and statements 
on economic and trade relations. Issues connected with 
Ukraine's fulfillment of the START I Treaty and with making the 
mechanism of granting American aid more concrete are also to be 
discussed. A meeting is planned with the leadership of the 
International Monetary Fund and the World Bank. Their 
investments are to be included in the Ukrainian reforms." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

