<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hryb Grants Interview </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2802141594 Minsk ZVYAZDA in Belarusian 25 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> WS2802141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk ZVYAZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Supreme Soviet Chairman Mechyslaw Hryb by </F>
Vital Tshygankov; place and date not given: "The Belarusian and 
Russian Prime Ministers Will Meet in Early March"] 
  [Text] During a recess at the Supreme Soviet session, 
journalists interviewed Mechyslaw Hryb, head of the legislature. 
  [Tsygankov] What is your attitude toward the proposal by one 
of the Russian Duma legislative factions about the political 
unification of Belarus with Russia? 
  [Hryb] This issue was never discussed -- either at the 
meeting of the prime ministers in Moscow or the 
Interparliamentary Assembly in Saint Petersburg. We are 
interested only in an economic union and a common ruble zone. I 
can assure you that no official circles ever considered the 
political union. 
  [Tsygankov] When will the Belarusian prime minister go to 
Moscow? 
  [Hryb] As is known, both prime ministers are ill now. Once 
they begin to recover, I think their meeting will actually take 
place. I talked with Kebich -- the government heads are 
planning to meet in early March. Viktor Chernomyrdin even 
called off his foreign visits. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

