<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich Favors Democratic Electoral Bloc </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0103102694 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0400 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0103102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Former Supreme Soviet Chairman Stanislav 
Shushkevich in an interview to INTERFAX has spoken in favor of 
creating an electoral bloc of democratic forces in the republic. 
According to the ex-speaker, this bloc could consist of various 
social and political organizations, including the oppositional 
Belarusian Popular Front. Having suggested that he will 
actively participate in the formation of such a bloc, 
Shushkevich stated that for the time being, he does not intend 
to create a party of his own. It is necessary to urge early 
parliamentary elections, which were promised by the Supreme 
Soviet to the people some time ago, noted the ex-speaker. 

</TEXT>

