<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Spring 94' Urges Shushkevich Candidacy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2802200394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1815 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2802200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] People's Deputy Stanislav Shushkevich held two 
meetings with workers in Mogilev this past Sunday [27 February]. 
The former parliamentary speaker sees early parliamentary 
elections as the way out of the current difficult situation. 
Touching upon the unification of monetary systems of Russia and 
Belarus, Stanislav Shushkevich spoke in favor of this agreement 
concluded on equal conditions without infringing upon the 
interests of our Republic. 
  The leaders of the local "Spring 94" bloc of democratic 
forces publicized an appeal to Stanislav Shushkevich, in which 
they requested that he put forward his candidacy for the post of 
Belarus' first president. This appeal was approved by the 
supporters of democratic parties. 

</TEXT>

