<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Releases Results </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802210194 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
2000 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2802210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Mircea Dascaliuc report from Chisinau] </F>
  [Text] After having entered into the computers the 
election results coming from 82 percent of the total number of 
electoral constituencies on the entire territory of the Republic 
of Moldova, this evening the Central Electoral Commission 
released for the mass media the rating of the first seven 
political forces, as follows: 
  The Agrarian Democratic Party -- 43.21 percent; 
  The Bloc of the Socialist Party and the Edinstvo Unity 
Movement -- 21.77 percent; 
  The Bloc of Peasants and Intellectuals -- 8.98 percent; 
  The Christian-Democratic Popular Front Alliance -- 7.31 
percent; 
  The Social-Democratic Party -- 3.51 percent; 
  The Democratic Party of Labor -- 2.55 percent; 
  The Reform Party -- 2.46 percent. 
  The chairman of the Central Electoral Commission said that 
tomorrow they will proceed to examine the electoral documents 
that were sent to them by each electoral constituency. The 
chairman also pointed out that he firmly rejects all assertions 
circulating false data claiming that the source was the Central 
Electoral Commission. He also mentioned the fact that the 
results that have been published until now do not have an 
absolute value and do not represent the final results of the 27 
February elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

