<H3> <TI>   Azeri Attack on Gadrut Repulsed 27 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2802123494 Yerevan SNARK in English 1210 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2802123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, February 28 (SNARK) -- Three armoured 
units and dozens of soldiers killed -- these are the losses the 
Azerbaijani side suffered as a result of yesterday's offensive 
in the Gadrut direction of Karabakh front. As SNARK was 
informed in the press-center of Karabakh Defence Army, by the 
evening of February 27 the defenders of Karabakh had managed to 
repel the enemy's attack and made him retreat to the initial 
positions. On Karabakh side there are 8 soldiers killed and one 
wounded. 
  Today at the greater part of the front line there is 
relative 
peace, occasionally violated by short exchange of fire. 
  Meanwhile, according to Karabakh Defence Army data, the 
accumulation of Azerbaijani man power and military hardware is 
observed at eastern part of the front. 

</TEXT>

