<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Procurator-General Says `Coup' Planned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802222994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1800 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802222994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Mais Mamedov] A whole arms depot has been 
discovered by law enforcement bodies of Baku in the headquarters 
of the Azerbaijan People's Front. It consists of 42 projectiles 
for grenade launchers, about 200 bottles of inflammable liquid, 
73 bullet proof vests, fuses for grenades, and smoke pots. 
  Speaking today at a press conference, procurator-general of 
the republic Ali Omerov stated that according to information at 
his disposal the People's Front of Azerbaijan had been preparing 
a coup for 5 March. He also announced that in a number of 
districts of Azerbaijan today members of that organization had 
been detained and combat weaponry had been confiscated from 
them. Those arrested include citizens from Chechnya. 
  Minister of Internal Affairs Vafig Novruzov [as heard] 
described as ridiculous claims of the People's Front leadership 
that the weaponry had been deliberately planted by policemen to 
settle scores with members of that organization. He pointed ou 
that an inquiry was being conducted which would dot all the "i"s. 

</TEXT>

