<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armenia Holding 16 Azerbaijani POWs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802183394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1702 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At present there are 16 Azeri prisoners of war in 
Armenia, which has been confirmed by the International Red 
Cross, the chief of the press center of Armenia's Defence 
Ministry, Gagik Martoian, told Interfax. He qualified the 
recent Azeri radio allegations that Armenia is holding 3500 
Azeri prisoners of war, as "another lie." 
  According to Martoian, 5 Azeris were captured "when staging 
armed encroachment on Armenia's borders," and 11 when trying to 
cross Armenian territory from Azerbaijan to Nakhichevan. 
  Moreover, the Defence Ministry spokesman denied the Azeri 
Foreign Ministry's assertions that there are concentration camps 
in Armenia. 
  As Martoian said, last year Armenia unilaterally returned to 
Azerbaijan 16 prisoners of war and 60 civilians from Kelbajar 
District in Azerbaijan, who had taken refuge in the canyons of 
Vardeni District in Armenia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

