<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion Termed `Sabotage' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103105194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1007 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Kuchina] </F>
  [Text] Riga, 1 Mar -- Restoration work has started today on 
the site of the explosion which took place yesterday five km 
from the Russian radar station in the Latvian village of 
Skrunda. One of the masts of the electric power line supplying 
electricity to the station was damaged here. A commission 
consisting of representatives of the station, Latvenergo 
[Latvian power supply company], and the criminal police have 
officially established that this was an act of sabotage. In 
connection with this, the press center of the North-Western 
Group of Forces reports, the Russian embassy is preparing a note 
of protest to the Latvian Foreign Ministry. Leonid Mayorov, 
commander of the group of forces, sent a request to the 
procurator general of Latvia. 

</TEXT>

