<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brazauskas Views Lithuanian-Polish Joint Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802161094 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1200 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas thinks that 
the jointly coordinated draft Lithuanian-Polish state treaty 
addresses the integrity of both states and the inviolability of 
state borders. The president said at a news conference today 
that the current mutual relations between both countries and 
prospects for future cooperation were adequately described in 
the draft treaty. 
  Answering a question of whether the property would be 
returned to the Polish public organizations which were active in 
the occupied Vilnius region in 1920-39, President Algirdas 
Brazauskas pointed out that this was not envisaged by the 
Lithuanian constitution. 
  According to the president, similar questions were raised by 
Jewish organizations in Israel. However, the two conditions 
envisaged for the reimbursement of private or state property say 
that persons claiming back their property must be citizens of 
Lithuania and reside permanently in Lithuania. If it is proved 
that these conditions are fulfilled then their property will be 
returned, regardless of their nationality, the president said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

