<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Meets Shumeyko, Rybkin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103133994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1106 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0103133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On Tuesday in the Kremlin, Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin met with Chairman of Russian Federal Assembly's 
Federation Council Vladimir Shumeyko. Our Interfax 
correspondent learned that during the conversation the officials 
discussed issues related to the work plans of the parliament's 
upper chamber. In particular, they spoke about settlement of 
the Ossetian-Ingush conflict, in light of upcoming discussion of 
this issue in the parliament, they also touched upon relations 
with Chechnya. 
  Shumeyko also informed the president about the likelihood of 
the Civil Code coming up for consideration in the Federation 
Council. 
  Yeltsin and Shumeyko discussed the situation in the country 
in detail in the context of the amnesty announced by the State 
Duma. 
  On the same day Yeltsin is to meet with the State Duma 
speaker Ivan Rybkin. 

</TEXT>

