<H3> <TI>   1991 Coup Trial Discontinued in Wake of Amnesty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103132894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1300 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0103132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Belskiy] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 1 TASS -- Following the release of 
October armed revolt organisers, the trial of 1991 abortive 
Soviet coup leaders was declared over on Tuesday. 
  On the basis of the political amnesty proclaimed by the 
State 
Duma the court ruled to drop criminal proceedings against former 
Soviet top officials who organised the 1991 August coup in 
Moscow. 
  The political amnesty proclaimed by Duma covered the 1991 
coup plotters, organisers of the 1993 armed opposition revolt in 
Moscow and of the May Day demonstration last year. All the 
three events resulted in bloodshed. 

</TEXT>

