<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reaction to Amnesty, Release of Prisoners </TI></H3>
<H4>   Rybkin `Confused' Over Swift Release </H4>
<F P=102> LD2802164894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1436 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Speaker of the Duma Ivan Rybkin at a meeting of 
senior parliamentary officials on Monday said he was confused 
over the undue haste with which the Prosecutor General's Office 
had ordered the release of the leaders of the October uprising 
from Moscow's Lefortovo prison. 
  This follows a statement from Defense Committee chairman 
Sergey Yushenkov who represented the Russia's Choice Party at 
the meeting. In his words, the speaker said that former 
prosecuter general Aleksey Kazannik had sent him a letter on 
Saturday asking how to implement the Duma amnesty resolution but 
announced his resignation later in the day without waiting for 
reply. 
  Yushenkov said that as soon as the Duma reconvened on March 
11, a draft resolution would be put up for discussion warning 
the uprising leaders that the amnesty could be withdrawn if they 
violated Article 70 of the Criminal Code. The article spells 
out punishment measures against organizers of mass riots. 

</TEXT>

