<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Creates Financial-Budget Department </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802210394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1853 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow February 28 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin signed a decree on Monday creating a new presidential 
financial-budget department within his administration. 
  According to the presidential press service, the department 
will supply the president with information and analytical 
assistance in the sphere of state finances, budget, insurance, 
prices, credits and money circulation. 
  The new body will also prepare practical recommendations on 
issues of finances and monetary policy. 
  Igor Moskovskiy was appointed head of the presidential 
financial-budget department, the press service said. 

</TEXT>

