<H3> <TI>   Moskovskiy Named Head </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0103125094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 1 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK0103125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: Russian President's Finance-Budget </F>
Administration in the Making"] 
  [Text] Boris Yeltsin signed an edict yesterday on the 
formation of a finance-budget administration of the Russian 
Federation president within the head of state's staff. The new 
subdivision "is being created for the information and analytical 
support of the Russian president's activity in the area of 
statewide finances, budget, insurance, pricing, credit 
relations, and money circulation, as well as for preparing 
practical recommendations on conceptual and strategic questions 
of the finance-budget, taxation, monetary, and hard currency 
problems." Igor Moskovskiy was appointed its head. 

