<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces To Be Reorganized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802133894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1240 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 28 Feb -- All forms of the Armed Forces of 
Russia without exception will be subjected to internal 
reorganization aimed at reducing them in the near future. This 
was stated today by Colonel General Mikhail Kolesnikov, chief of 
General Staff of the Armed Forces of Russia, replying to a 
question from the ITAR-TASS correspondent regarding the fate of 
anti-aircraft defense, the Navy, and other structures of the 
Defense Department. He did, however, point out specifically 
that the Ministry of Defense is not yet "ready to bring all the 
arms of the forces into a single integrated structure." Any 
reshaping will, in the opinion of the military leader, 
invariably bring in its wake disruption of the administration 
system, which must not be permitted. 

</TEXT>

