<H3> <TI>   Duma Chairman Receives Released Prisoner </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802192094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1516 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 28 Feb -- Journalists noticed today that one 
of those freed from the Lefortovo prison, Andrey Dunayev, was in 
the State Duma. He went to the 18th floor where the office of 
Duma Chairman Ivan Rybkin is situated. 
  For a comment on this fact one can quote Georgiy Satarov, 
the 
Russian Federation president's aide, who said today that after 
speaking to Ivan Rybkin, it became clear to him that the 
chairman of the chamber and its deputies feel that they are 
responsible for the behavior of those whom they had freed. In 
order to preserve their reputation of supporters of reforms, the 
Duma leaders are apparently trying to obtain promises of 
trustworthiness from the organizers of the October events in 
Moscow. 

</TEXT>

