<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gromov, Samsonov Named CIS Defense Ministers Council Heads </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0103090094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 1 Mar 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK0103090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Round the Clock Non-Stop" </F>
rubric: "Boris Gromov Becomes Chairman"] 
  [Text] The reforming of the CIS Joint Armed Forces High 
Command got under way as of yesterday. The new structure -- a 
staff for coordination and cooperation -- will be more 
international. Whereas the majority of positions were taken 
earlier by officers of Russia, now 50 percent of the staff has 
been assigned to the republics. But the collective security 
will be financed in the same proportion. 
  All in all, there will remain 240 people on the staff's 
payroll. Its work will be directed by the chairman of the 
Defense Ministers council. This position will be filled in turn 
by generals from all the republics. Russian Deputy Defense 
Minister Boris Gromov has been appointed the first chairman. 
The new staff will also have a permanent position, that of 
deputy chairman. He will be Colonel General Samsonov, chief of 
staff of the CIS Joint Armed Forces High Command. The deputy 
chairman was also granted the right to vote over Russia's 
objections. 

</TEXT>

