<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hryb Urges Economic Union With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0203103094 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0400 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0203103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mechyslaw Hryb, new speaker of the Belarusian 
parliament, has spoken in favor of urgently reestablishing 
economic ties with former republics of the USSR, in particular, 
with Russia. In an interview with Moscow PRAVDA, he said that 
the only way out of the crisis for Belarus leads through an 
economic union and a single monetary system with Russia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-14981 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov041_g_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-041 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Head Hryb Criticizes Press Attacks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0103150494 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1300 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0103150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mikhail Rudkowski] </F>
  [Excerpts] Today's session of the Supreme Soviet will see 
the announcement of the results of a roll-call vote on a package 
of bills related to the Constitution of the Republic of Belarus. 
One of these issues is the introduction of the post of 
president as the head of state and executive branch. The 
official results will be made known at 1800. With regard to the 
president -- who is eligible for this post and how they will be 
elected -- by nationwide elections or by people's deputies in 
this Oval Room? -- the Supreme Soviet should adopt an 
appropriate law. This extremely important issue concerning 
presidential elections is now in the hands of the people's 
deputies. [passage omitted] 
  Before discussion of the agenda for today's session, the 
Supreme Soviet was addressed by Chairman Mechyslaw Ivanavich 
Hryb. Here is an excerpt from his address: 
  [Begin Hryb recording] For some time now, especially after 
my election to the post of Supreme Soviet chairman, some media, 
in particular the papers SVABODA [in Minsk] and IZVESTIYA, 
started publishing reports that do not correspond to the facts. 
These publications compromise me as a man and the chairman of 
the Supreme Soviet. Esteemed People's Deputies! I want to 
assure you: It is not a question of my inability to defend my 
dignity and honor, to obtain justice in a legal way through the 
courts, and to punish the guilty. By the way, it happened once 
with regard to the SVABODA newspaper. The question is that I do 
not have time to bring any action in the courts. Therefore, I 
am forced to address you, People's Deputies, respected electors, 
and citizens of the Republic, and assure you that my program and 
my demands for establishing order and discipline in the 
Republic, as well as to strengthen the fight against crime are 
not liked by everyone. However, I assure all citizens of our 
Republic that I will not retreat from this course. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-14982 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov041_g_94003" </HT>


