<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Reportedly Approves Presidential Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103124394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1106 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0103124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to unofficial information, which INTERFAX 
has obtained from the Belarusian parliament's Tallying 
Commission, the required number of votes has been secured for 
the introduction of the presidential post in this republic. 
  The Belarusian parliament continues personalized voting on 
the basic provisions of the draft constitution. The official 
results will be summed up in the evening of March 1. 
  The basic provisions of the Belarussian Constitution will be 
adopted if at least 232 deputies vote for them. The Counting 
Commission told Interfax that by the end of the morning session, 
more than 240 deputies had cast their votes in their favor. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

