<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament To Continue Activity </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0103164494 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1840 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0103164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 28/2/1994 -- Old parliament's 
leadership and members of Parliamentary Presidium, total 26 
persons, will keep their status and will activate until the day 
of first session of the newly elected parliament. This first 
session is planned for March 15th, stated to BASA Pavel Rotaru, 
from the Parliamentary Press Service. Before February 27th, 
former MP's should have abandoned their ID's and diplomatic 
passports. Parliament commissions have formally finished their 
existence on the eve of elections, but most deputies engaged in 
commissions are still in offices in the parliament building, 
said Rotaru. He noted that the future MP's will enjoy the 
parliament's rooms and services only after the Central Electoral 
Commission confirm their status and their mandates are validated 
during first sessions of the new parliament. 

</TEXT>

