<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Presents New Air Force Commander </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0103190694 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 26 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0103190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "No to Rally Passions Within Troops!"] </F>
  [Text] Ukraine's minister of defense, Army General V. 
Radetskyy, visited a garrison stationed in Vinnytsya Oblast. 
  During the meeting with officers and generals at the 
headquarters of Ukraine's Air Force, Vitaliy Radetskyy stressed 
that the merger of the Air Force and Air Defense has been 
suspended. It is necessary to work on this problem as a 
promising one. The defense minister presented the new Air Force 
commander -- Lieutenant General Volodymyr Antonets, appointed to 
the post by a Ukrainian presidential edict. 
  "We are military people and must fulfill our supreme 
commander's order," commented the minister upon the changes in 
the personnel. "Rally passions within troops are 
inadmissible...." 
  Radetskyy also met with officers of the command of the 43d 
Strategic Rocket Troops and stressed once again that Ukraine is 
a missile and space power, and that even after the program for 
nuclear disarmament is completed, missile specialists will have 
to fulfill specific work for the defense of our country. 

</TEXT>

