<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean President Gets Parties' Support </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0103164794 Simferopol KRYMSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 22 Feb 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> WS0103164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Simferopol KRYMSKAYA PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by l. Ryabchikov: "Parties Are Ready To Help the </F>
President"] 
  [Text] On 19 February, Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov met 
with leaders of officially registered parties. During their 
meeting, participants detailed their stances, the attitude 
toward the program of the president, changes in the Republic, 
and what assistance they require. The leaders of the parties, 
including the Party of Crimean Economic Revival and the 
Ukrainian parties, declared their readiness to promote the 
implementation of economic reform. 
  The meeting was held in a constructive atmosphere, stated 
Agrarian Party Deputy Chairman Mikhail Frolov. We favor social 
justice for workers of the agricultural sector, the issuing of 
additional benefits which are necessary for the development of 
the agricultural sector. In this respect, the stance of the 
president coincides with ours. 
  We came with a package of proposals, said Yefim Fiks, 
chairman of the Party of Social Guarantees, and the president 
suggested that edicts be drafted by us on the basis of our 
proposals. 
  Participants in the meeting spoke of the need to adopt a 
joint statement of all the political forces of the Republic in 
support of the president's actions. 
  When Sergey Nikulin, presidential adviser for relations with 
parties and public organizations, commented on this meeting, he 
noted that Yuriy Mechkov asked all the participants to forward 
proposals for candidates to vacancies in all state bodies. In 
the opinion of Nikulin, the consolidation will make it possible 
to create a powerful bloc supporting the course of the 
president. This will be a new kind of legislature, he stressed. 

</TEXT>

