<H3> <TI>   Last Strategic Bombers Leave Kazakhstan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103221394 Moscow Radio Moscow in Russian to Tajikistan 
1700 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103221394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Radio Slavyanka" program of the Russian Defense </F>
Ministry] 
  [Text] In accordance with the obligations undertaken by 
Russia within its rights as legal successor to the former USSR, 
the last four of 40 TU-95 MS strategic missile-carrying aircraft 
based near Semipalatinsk have left Kazakhstan. Some old-model 
TU-95 aircraft remain in Kazakhstan that experts believe no 
longer represent a real threat to anyone. 

</TEXT>

