<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Warns on Azeri Cease-Fire Violation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0103135994 Yerevan SNARK in English 1045 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0103135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, March 1 (SNARK)--The Azerbaijani side 
violated the armistice on cease-fire from 00:00, 1st of March. 
The armistice was achieved through the mediation of the Russian 
Defense Minister Pavel Grachev. 
  The Press-Service of the Karabakh Defense Army told SNARK 
last night and this morning the positions of the Karabakh troops 
at some parts of the front, in particular, at the northern 
Martuninskiy region, were under the artillery shellings. The 
Karabakh side suffers 3 soldiers wounded. Following the terms 
of the armistice treaty Karabakh defenders made no retaliative 
actions. 
  In connection with the action Seyran Oganyan, the Head of 
the 
Staff of the Karabakh Defense Army, made a declaration which 
says that the Karabakh side will have to undertake the adequate 
measures if Azeris go on with the armistice violations. 

</TEXT>

