<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Protests Azeri Air Raids </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0103203894 Yerevan SNARK in English 1411 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0103203894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, March 1 (SNARK)--During a period of last 6 
months Azerbaijani military aircraft more than ten times entered 
air space of Armenia and "layed eggs" in the border adjusting 
regions, the letter of Armenian Foreign Minister Vahan Papazyan 
sent to Beniamino Andreata, an acting Chairman of the CSCE, and 
Manfred Woerner, NATO General Secretary. 
  Document also says that during a period of 1993 Azerbaijani 
aircraft did more than 50 military air-raids to the Republic of 
Nagorno-Karabakh. 
  Mr. Papazyan attracts the attention of the CSCE and NATO 
leadership to the fact that Azerbaijan doesn't follow his 
obligations mentioned in the Treaty of Conventional Armaments in 
Europe. In particular, making a 1992-1993 annual report 
Azerbaijan deviated from supplying with the information on 
military airdromes where the military air-raids are undertaking 
from. A considerable lack of correspondence on the existence, 
reduction of the warplanes quantity and their losses is typical 
for the informational documents. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

