<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Appeals Subjection to `Persecution' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0203115094 Baku TURAN in English 1119 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0203115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (March 1) TURAN--"Recently the pressure on the 
democracy and freedom of speech in Azerbaijan intensified", says 
distributed today appeal of Baku's newspaper "AZADLYG." The 
document reports that newspaper "AZADLYG" has been openly 
subjecting to persecution for the last time. 
  During the past days the police of Baku's Sabail region has 
been repeatedly searching the building of the editing house of 
the newspaper. The policemen armed with machine guns encircled 
the building. 
  The representatives of the police and the authorities gave 
no 
details of their activities to the journalists. 
  The police seized a room in the editing house of the 
newspaper by force. Today's issue of "AZADLYG" is banned by the 
political censorship. 
  This morning the employees of located there organizations 
"AZADLYG", and TURAN NEWS AGENCY were not allowed to enter the 
building. 
  In this connection "AZADLYG" newspaper addressed an appeal 
to 
the world community and Baku-based foreign Embassies. It says 
that basic democratic freedoms are brutally violated in 
Azerbaijan. 
  "We hope that World Democratic Institutions will express 
their attitude towards present situation in Azerbaijan", 
stresses this document. 
  It should be stressed that independent "AZADLYG" newspaper 
has the biggest circulation in Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

