<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on AZADLYG, TURAN Troubles </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0203115994 Baku TURAN in English 1119 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0203115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (March 1) TURAN--Today at 17.00 the police left 
the building of the editorial office where the leading 
opposition newspaper of Azerbaijan, AZADLYG, is located on 
Khagani 33 Street. 
  Also located in that building are the independent TURAN NEWS 
AGENCY, Democracy Development Fund, Cultural Fund "Yurd", the 
Independent Centre for Economic and Political Researches and the 
International Centre "Polyglot". 
  During the past three days the police, armed with machine 
guns, as well as employees of the Procurator's Office of the 
republic, continued their searches of offices in the building, 
and checked people entering and exiting the building. 
  Today the journalists of "AZADLYG" and TURAN NEWS AGENCY 
held 
a joint press conference and provided details about the 
arbitrary lawlessness of the police to foreign diplomats and 
journalists. 
  Having found nothing in the rooms and basements of the 
building, the police and the employees of the Procurator's 
office were compelled to leave. Earlier they had said that 
"journalists hid weapons and ammunition in the rooms." But 
having found nothing, the policemen seized several issues of 
TURAN daily news reports and several issues of independent 
newspaper, CHESHME ("MOSAIC"). 
  Due to the lawlessness by the police, the employees of Turan 
news agency and the remaining organizations located in the 
building were unable to work for the entire day. 

</TEXT>

