<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Constitution Provides for Unitarian State </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203140094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1237 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0203140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Albert Kochetkov] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi March 2 TASS -- Georgia's new constitution 
provides for the building of a unitarian state with autonomies, 
a constitutional commission member told ITAR-TASS. He said the 
draft of the new constitution has been finalized, although some 
politicians in the republic have stated their preference for the 
federation idea. 
  But even federalists insist that the component parts of a 
Georgian Federation should not be granted the right of 
secession. They believe nonetheless that this would remove 
support for separatism and help the republic to get rid of 
conflicts on the ethnic grounds. 

</TEXT>

