<H3> <TI>   Official Comments on Armenian Declarations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0103211694 Yerevan SNARK in English 1559 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0103211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, March 1 (SNARK)--Aleksandr Kavsadze, 
chairman of the Human Rights' Protection commission of the 
Georgian Parliament expressed his bewilderment on the recent 
declarations of Armenian leaders. 
  The other day Armenian Foreign Minister Vahan Papazyan 
declared that Georgia will have nothing to do but to accept 
Armenian provisions. Earlier Armenia suggested to exchange some 
amount of gas, bought by her from Turkmenistan, with free 
shipment through Georgian territory. 
  "Such declarations won't promote our relations", Aleksandr 
Kavsadze told SNARK. In his opinion, "when the situation is 
difficult you should not to make such statements but to solve 
all the problems in consent. Moreover it is inadmissible to 
scare each other," said Georgian Deputy. 

</TEXT>

