<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Forces Issue Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103115394 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1100 GMT 1 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On Sunday night [as heard], a pylon of a 110 kv 
high-tension power line between Broceni and Skrunda, 3 km from 
the Skrunda radar station, was blown up. An investigation into 
the incident is currently under way. The explosives used have 
not been identified yet. The Skrunda radar station is still 
receiving power via another power line from Tukums. Valdis 
Lidumnieks, head of the Broceni substation group of the 
high-tension power network, reports that the power supply via 
the damaged line will be resumed today. 
  The press center of the Northwestern Group of [Russian] 
Forces circulated a statement today saying that a joint 
commission of representatives of Latvenergo, the criminal 
police, and the Skrunda radar station assessed the explosion as 
an act of sabotage. A rapid reaction group from the Ministry of 
Internal Affairs, headed by Gunars Liepins, the senior 
investigator of the Latvian prosecutor's office for particularly 
serious (?cases), has left for the scene of the incident. 

</TEXT>

