<F P=102>  LD0103230294 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 2100 GMT 1 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103230294 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The explosion of a pylon on the electricity line 
supplying electric power to the Russian military site was 
sabotage. [passage omitted] Here is Ritums Rozenbergs reporting 
by phone from Moscow: 
  [Rozenbergs] Commenting on the blowing up of an electricity 
pylon of the Skrunda military site, (Sergey Grikhayko), head of 
the Baltic Department of the Russian Foreign Ministry, stated 
the following: We hope that the Latvian authorities will adopt 
all necessary measures to clarify the causes and perpetrators of 
the incident, and we hope that this action will not affect the 
talks by our groups of experts and will not disturb the 
documents we have agreed on for the short term and the 
agreements signed on military questions. 
  It seems that the Russian side's reaction to the explosion 
of 
the pylon will not arouse broad debate. At the moment Russia 
has on its agenda questions of a much more serious scale. 
First, the spy trial has to be concluded; second, it has to go 
on settling the question of the Bosnian Serbs; third, the debate 
on the consequences of the amnesty has to be concluded. Ritums 
Rozenbergs, special correspondent for the newspaper LABRIT in 
Moscow, specially for Latvian Radio. 

