<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rybkin Warns Coup Plotters Against Destabilization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103140694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1315 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondents Pavel Kuznetsov </F>
and Ivan Novikov] 
  [Text] Moscow, 1 March -- The Council of the State Duma 
believes that the amnesty decision provides thousands of 
Russians who have newly acquired freedom to become actively 
involved in the creative work of all constructive public forces 
for the benefit of the country, stated Ivan Rybkin, who held a 
press conference in the State Duma today. 
  He read out a statement by the chamber's Council adopted 
yesterday. The statement says that if any of those amnestied 
"lacks the brains, common sense, heart, or desire to take the 
path of accord, the State Duma, in accordance with the spirit 
and letter of the decisions adopted and together with the 
president, will find an opportunity to take measures to prevent 
the situation in the country being destabilized." 
  Ivan Rybkin underlined that the State Duma is ready to study 
constructive proposals for a mechanism to implement the amnesty 
resolutions adopted by the Chamber, as well as to study a draft 
of a memorandum agreed with other bodies of state power about 
the responsibility of government institutions and politicians to 
preserve civil peace and public order in Russia. 
  The chairman of the State Duma said that the decisions on 
the 
amnesty were dictated by a strong conviction that Russia cannot 
be saved from a national crisis without an amnesty for all the 
participants of the notorious events in 1991 and 1993, just as 
it is impossible to achieve this without a stable civil peace. 
He underlined that during a debate of the amnesty question at a 
session of the chamber, the absolute majority of deputies 
jointly reached a formula for a achieving civil peace and 
national accord. It is based on a constructive cooperation with 
the president, all power structures, and political forces and is 
aimed at strengthening society and understanding the great 
responsibility for the rebirth of statehood and the creation of 
a new Russia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

