<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Official Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0103204194 Tallinn BNS in English 1720 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0103204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Tallinn, Mar 01, BNS -- Alexandr Udaltsov, a 
senior official at the Russian Foreign Ministry in charge of 
Baltic affairs, today voiced his surprise at Estonian Foreign 
Ministry statement. 
  Udaltsov told BNS Estonia "is long since familiar with 
Russia's official position" on troop withdrawal, which does not 
accept Aug. 31 as the final, mutually agreed upon deadline for 
the pullout of its armed forces from Estonia. 
  "It is unclear why (Estonia) attempts to build this position 
up as a news item," the Russian diplomat said. "If the Estonian 
side is seeking a pretext to break off the talks, Estonians 
should admit they see no point in continuing the negotiations." 
[passage omitted] 
  Estonian Prime Minister Mart Laar said at a press conference 
today that, if Russia officially announces it will change the 
troop withdrawal deadline, Estonia will break off the talks. 
  "The pullout of Russian troops from Estonia has slowed down 
since the beginning of the year," the premier noted. "If Russia 
had continued the withdrawal at the same pace as in past years, 
the troops would have left Estonia in the first months of this 
year." 

</TEXT>

