<H3> <TI>   President Remains Most Popular Politician </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0103161294 Tallinn BNS in English 1330 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0103161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Mar 01, BNS -- The most recent public 
opinion poll in Lithuania indicates that President Algirdas 
Brazauskas continues to top the list of most popular politicians 
after a year spent in office. 
  The principal tendency remains the same -- political leaders 
are gradually losing popularity. Aloyzas Sakalas, leader of the 
Social Democratic Party, was the only exception during the 
period between mid-January and mid-February. 
  The results of the poll conducted by the British-Lithuanian 
Baltic Surveys company suggest the following list of top ten 
Lithuanian politicians: 
  Algirdas Brazauskas -- 56 percent /-2/ 
  Egidijus Bickauskas -- 50 percent /-3/ 
  Romualdas Ozolas -- 46 percent /-1/ 
  Kazimieras Antanavicius -- 41 percent /0/ 
  Vytautas Landsbergis -- 35 percent /-5/ 
  Adolfas Slezevicius -- 33 percent /-4/ 
  Gediminas Vagnorius -- 28 percent /0/ 
  Aloyzas Sakalas -- 28 percent /+1/ 
  Ceslovas Jursenas -- 27 percent /-1/ 
  Povilas Gylys -- 18 percent /0/ 

</TEXT>

