<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defendants Warned Against Lawbreaking </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203113294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203113294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The investigation into the criminal case instituted 
with regard to the organization of mass unrest on 3-4 October 
1993 in the capital is continuing. This is set out in the 
statement from the information and public relations center of 
Russia's General Procuracy. It is noted in the report that the 
investigation has not yet been completed of the circumstances 
regarding the infliction of material damage, which, according to 
the legislation, is subject to compensation by those who are 
guilty of it. The investigation also needs to be completed 
regarding individuals who took advantage of the situation that 
had taken shape in Moscow from 21 September to 4 October 1933 
and committed thefts, acts of violence, deliberate hooliganism, 
and other breaches of the law. 
  The general procuracy stressed that if those amnestied take 
the path of unlawful action again, it will use all the powers 
granted to it by the law that has come into force where there 
are conditions of unavoidable liability. 

</TEXT>

