<H3> <TI>   Staff `Bewildered' by Ilyushenko Appointment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0203082094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 2 Mar 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK0203082094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["NG" report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Prosecutor's </F>
Office Bewildered"] 
  [Text] It has come to light that many among the 
prosecution staff are bewildered by the decision to appoint 
Aleksey Ilyushenko, former head of the Control Administration of 
the Russian Federation president's staff, as acting general 
prosecutor of the Russian Federation. Ilyushenko actively 
worked for the Interdepartmental Commission on Combating Crime 
and Corruption which was gathering damning evidence against some 
prominent figures of the Russian opposition, in particular 
against Aleksandr Rutskoy. A check on the information gathered 
by the Interdepartmental Commission was entrusted to the Moscow 
Prosecutor's Office. Some time later, it concluded that the 
charges of financial machinations against the former Russian 
vice president were unsupportable. Following this, a decision 
was made to institute a criminal libel suit. Theoretically, 
those to be tried were former members of the above 
Interdepartmental Commission, including Mr. Ilyushenko. One 
high-ranking Moscow Prosecutor's Office staffer has promised to 
speak to NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA on this score in greater detail. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

