<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Edict on General Prosecutor's Resignation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0103161194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 1 Mar 94 
Second Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM0103161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Edict No. 391 of the Russian Federation President dated </F>
Moscow, The Kremlin, 26 February 1994 and signed by Russian 
Federation President B. Yeltsin: "On The Russian Federation 
General Prosecutor"] 
  [Text] Russian Federation General Prosecutor A.I. Kazannik 
has tendered his resignation. 
  Guided by subpoint "F" of Article 83 of the Russian 
Federation Constitution I rule that: 
  1. A proposal on releasing Aleksey Ivanovich Kazannik from 
the post of Russian Federation general prosecutor at his own 
request should be submitted to the Russian Federation Federal 
Assembly Federation Council. 
  2. Aleksey Nikolayevich Ilyushenko should be presented to 
the Russian Federation Federal Assembly Federation Council as a 
candidate for appointment to the post of Russian Federation 
general prosecutor. 
  3. Until a Russian Federation general prosecutor is 
appointed his duties should be carried out by Aleksey 
Nikolayevich Ilyushenko. 
  4. This edict comes into force the moment it is signed. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated] Moscow, Moscow, 26 February 1994 

</TEXT>

